did.unittitle: Epsilon Sigma Phi, Alpha Omicron Chapter records
did.abstract: This collection documents the Cooperative Extension professional organization, Epsilon Sigma Phi, at Pennsylvania State University. The collection contains the constitution and bylaws, minutes, correspondence, agendas, committee member lists, and documentation on awards granted by the organization.
did.physloc: For current information on the location of these materials, please consult the Penn State University Libraries catalog via the link above. Archival collections may be housed in offsite storage. For materials stored offsite, please allow 2-3 business days for retrieval.

accessrestrict.head: Access Restrictions
accessrestrict.p: This collection is open for use only by verified members of the fraternity and/or researchers with written permission of the fraternity/sorority.
For information on accessing this collection please contact the Special Collections Research Services Unit at ul-spcolref@lists.psu.edu.

bioghist.head: Biographical or Historical Note
bioghist.p: Epsilon Sigma Phi, Alpha Omicron chapter, is a Cooperative Extension professional's organization. The Cooperative Extension System is a nationwide, non-credit educational network. Membership in Epsilon Sigma Phi, Alpha Omicron chapter is open to full-time faculty, professional, and administrative staff who have exhibited excellence in education and programming leadership and who have held part-time Extension appointments for at least two years.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: [Identification of item], Epsilon Sigma Phi, Alpha Omicron Chapter records, 00278, Eberly Family Special Collections Library, Pennsylvania State University.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This collection documents the Cooperative Extension professional organization, Epsilon Sigma Phi, at Pennsylvania State University. The collection contains the constitution and bylaws, minutes, correspondence, agendas, committee member lists, and documentation on awards granted by the organization.
